a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes f :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. x \<ge> 0 \<longrightarrow> f x = - x powr (1/3)"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. x < 0 \<longrightarrow> f x = x powr 2"
shows  "f (f (f (f 512))) = 16"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Let  \[ f(x) =
\begin{cases}
-\sqrt[3]x & \text{if } x \geq 0,\\
x^2& \text{if } x <0.
\end{cases}
\]Compute $f(f(f(f(512)))).$ The final Answer is 16
 ### Proof
 \begin{align} f(f(f(f(512)))) &=f(f(f(-8)))\\ &=f(f(64))\\ &=f(-4)\\ &=\boxed{16}. \end{align}
 *)
